  "translations": {
    "en": "So Hisham fell upon him and kissed his hands, his head and his feet, and said, 'This is enough for me, O son of the Messenger of God,' and he departed to his home. The next morning al-Daysani came to him and said, 'O Hisham! I came to you just to greet you, not to demand the answer.' So Hisham said to him, 'If you came to demand it, then here is the answer.'",
